  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The optimal antithrombotic therapy for patients requiring anticoagulation after coronary
      stenting is unknown. Double platelets suppressive agents combined with oral anticoagulation
      (triple antithrombotic therapy) remains the Gold standard.

      Our study aims at studying bleeding events occurring until 6 months after the initiation of
      triple antithrombotic therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
